Here are 2 songs from FSK's recent album "FSK International"

opening and closing low horn riff:

and then its back to the opening/closing riffs.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Medley:Was Kostet die Welt/Kleiner Polizist"


main chord structure is [ch]C[/ch]-[ch]Am[/ch]-[ch]F[/ch]-[ch]F[/ch]...very simple

[ch]C[/ch]   [ch]Am[/ch]         [ch]F[/ch]
Was Kostet die Welt?

[ch]C[/ch]            [ch]Am[/ch]     [ch]F[/ch]
Du bist mein bester Freund


then when David Lowery pauses in singing there is a riff:

    [ch]C[/ch]        [ch]Am[/ch]        [ch]F[/ch]
e-7-8-8-10-8-7-7-7-8-7-8-7---------|
B--------------------------10-8-10-|

and that repeats 3 or 4 times and then a G7 is played and we go to:

            [ch]C[/ch]    [ch]Am[/ch]   [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]F[/ch]
Kleiner Polizist,     die Welt ist Mist


which repeats and then ends on a C chord.


ill try to post more later, these songs are pretty simple, also,
translations are on the way.
